    • Method Detail

      • getPanel

        JPanel getPanel()
        Returns the exporter settings panel.
        Returns:
        a settings panel, or null

      • setup

        void setup(Exporter exporter)
        Link the UI to the exporter and therefore to settings values. This method is called after getPanel() to push settings.
        Parameters:
        exporter - the exporter that settings is to be set

      • unsetup

        void unsetup(boolean update)
        Notify UI the settings panel has been closed and that new values can be written.
        Parameters:
        update - true if user clicked OK or false if CANCEL.

      • isUIForExporter

        boolean isUIForExporter(Exporter exporter)
        Returns true if this UI belongs to the given exporter.
        Parameters:
        exporter - the exporter that has to be tested
        Returns:
        true if the UI is matching with exporter, false otherwise.

      • getDisplayName

        String getDisplayName()
        Returns the exporter display name
        Returns:
        the exporter display name
